theorem_statement: Let $N^p_{bin}(m)$ be the number of parts in the binary partitions of $m$. Define $s(0)=1$ and $s(m)=(-1)^{h(m)}$ for $m\geq 1$. Then we have \begin{equation} \sum_{k=1}^{n}N^p_{bin}(k)s(n-k)=\vartheta_2(n)+1. \end{equation}
